The paper discusses automatic machine learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of neural networks, evolutionary algorithms, and Bayesian optimization suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The mention of pipeline grammar and pre-trained models suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The use of benchmark datasets for classification and regression tasks suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of reproducible research suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category.
